HEADWORD: Potulent
<hw>Pot"u*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>potulentus</ets>, fr. <ets>potus</ets> a drinking, drink, fr.
<ets>potare</ets> to drink.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fit to drink;
potable.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nearly drunk; tipsy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pot-valiant</ent>⟦br⟧
